design parent

# The overlay RHS references `multiplier` (a parent-local parameter). In the *old*
# phased evaluator, params were partitioned by whether they (transitively) depended on
# external refs. Because `multiplier = 2 * src.base` does depend on `src.base`, it was
# scheduled to evaluate *after* refs — but the child's overlay is evaluated *during*
# the child's phase-2 setup, triggering a lookup of a not-yet-evaluated parent param
# and panicking.
#
# Under lazy evaluation, the overlay's cross-model lookup simply forces
# `parent.multiplier` on demand (which in turn forces `src.base`), so this file works.
#
# Expected: c.base = 2 * (2 * 3) = 12
base.c = 2 * multiplier
